<!--
===========================================================================
  test.xml — Anti-Aliasing + Refraction/Transparency test scene
===========================================================================

  SCENE LAYOUT:
    - 3 colored back walls (red/green/blue) at z=-6
    - Transparent glass cube in the middle around z=-3.5 (refraction test)
    - Gray floor at y=-1.5
    - Thin diagonal triangle in the top-right corner (AA test)
    - Two point lights

  VERTEX / UV / NORMAL LAYOUT (do NOT place XML comments inside
  <vertexdata>, <texturedata>, or <normaldata> — tinyxml2 GetText()
  stops at the first comment node):

    VERTICES (1-indexed):
      1-4   : Red back wall     (x: -3..-1, z=-6)
      5-8   : Green back wall   (x: -1..1,  z=-6)
      9-12  : Blue back wall    (x:  1..3,  z=-6)
      13-16 : Glass cube FRONT face  (z=-2.7)
      17-20 : Glass cube BACK face   (z=-4.3)
      21-24 : Floor                  (y=-1.5)
      25-27 : AA-test triangle       (top-right, z=-2.0)

    NORMALS (1-indexed):
      1: (0,0,1)   — walls, cube front, AA triangle
      2: (0,1,0)   — cube top, floor
      3: (0,0,-1)  — cube back
      4: (1,0,0)   — cube right
      5: (-1,0,0)  — cube left
      6: (0,-1,0)  — cube bottom

  ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
  FEATURE 1: ANTI-ALIASING
  ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
    Controlling tag:  <samples>N</samples>  (directly under <scene>)

    Test steps:
      1) <samples>1</samples>   -> aliased reference (current behavior)
      2) <samples>4</samples>   -> 4x (2x2 jittered) supersampling
      3) <samples>16</samples>  -> 16x (cleaner, slower)

    Where to look:
      - Diagonal edges of the yellow triangle (staircase artifacts)
      - Vertical seams between the red/green/blue walls
      - Edges of the glass cube

  ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
  FEATURE 2: REFRACTION / TRANSPARENCY
  ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
    Controlling tags (inside material id=4 "glass"):
      <refractionIndex>1.5</refractionIndex>   (glass 1.5, water 1.33, diamond 2.4)
      <transparency>0.9</transparency>         (0 = opaque, 1 = fully transparent)

    Test steps:
      A) Remove both tags and render
         -> Cube should be OPAQUE, standard Phong + mirror (control group)

      B) Only <transparency>0.9</transparency> active
         -> Green back wall should be visible through the cube, but NOT bent

      C) Both tags active (default)
         -> Rays passing through the cube show the green wall BENT
         -> Color shifts at the cube edges, total internal reflection on side faces

      D) <refractionIndex>1.0</refractionIndex> + transparency=0.9 (sanity check)
         -> Transparent but no bending

      E) <refractionIndex>2.4</refractionIndex> + transparency=0.9 (diamond)
         -> Extreme bending

  NOTE: maxraytracedepth=8 covers two surface crossings of the glass plus
  mirror bounces.
===========================================================================
-->
<scene>
    <samples>16</samples>
    <maxraytracedepth>8</maxraytracedepth>
    <background>10 10 15</background>

    <camera>
        <position>0 0 2</position>
        <gaze>0 0 -1</gaze>
        <up>0 1 0</up>
        <nearplane>-0.75 0.75 -0.75 0.75</nearplane>
        <neardistance>1</neardistance>
        <imageresolution>800 800</imageresolution>
    </camera>

    <lights>
